---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { SITE } from "../../config/site";

const title = `Topics | ${SITE.name}`;
const description =
  "Topic hubs that connect calculators with guides for APR, credit cards, and mortgage payoff workflows. Educational use only.";
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} canonicalPath="/topics">
  <section class="card hero">
    <nav class="breadcrumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <a href="/">Home</a>
      <span aria-hidden="true">/</span>
      <span aria-current="page">Topics</span>
    </nav>
    <h1>Topics</h1>
    <p>
      These hub pages connect calculators and guides into simple workflows, so users can understand assumptions and compare scenarios
      consistently. Start with the <a href="/calculators/apr-calculator">APR calculator</a>,{" "}
      <a href="/calculators/credit-card-payoff-calculator">credit card payoff calculator</a>, or{" "}
      <a href="/calculators/extra-payment-calculator">mortgage payoff calculator</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card section prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">How to use topic pages</h2>
    <ol class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; padding-left:18px">
      <li>Start with the core calculator to model your baseline.</li>
      <li>Read the linked guide to understand assumptions and common pitfalls.</li>
      <li>Change one input at a time to compare scenarios fairly (fees, rate, payment, or extra amount).</li>
      <li>Use the FAQ sections on calculator pages for edge cases and limitations.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="card section prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">Pick the right topic</h2>
    <ul class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; padding-left:18px">
      <li>APR: comparing loan offers with fees and different terms using the <a href="/calculators/apr-calculator">APR calculator</a>.</li>
      <li>Credit cards: payoff timelines, interest cost, and minimum payment risks with the <a href="/calculators/credit-card-payoff-calculator">credit card payoff calculator</a>.</li>
      <li>Mortgage payoff: monthly costs, amortization, and extra principal strategies in the <a href="/calculators/extra-payment-calculator">mortgage payoff calculator</a>.</li>
      <li>Refinance: compare costs, payment changes, and break-even timing with the <a href="/topics/refinance">refinance workflow</a>.</li>
      <li>Debt-to-income: estimate affordability and improve your ratio using the <a href="/calculators/debt-to-income-calculator">DTI calculator</a>.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="card section prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">How to compare scenarios safely</h2>
    <ul class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; padding-left:18px">
      <li>Change only one input at a time (rate, term, fee, or extra payment).</li>
      <li>Keep the baseline constant across comparisons.</li>
      <li>Use the same assumption about timing (e.g., when an extra payment posts).</li>
      <li>If results look surprising, verify the note rate vs APR and the remaining term.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="card section prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">Common mistakes across topics</h2>
    <ul class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; padding-left:18px">
      <li>Mixing escrow items with principal-and-interest calculations.</li>
      <li>Comparing monthly payment changes without checking total interest.</li>
      <li>Assuming extra payments reduce the required payment without a recast.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="card section prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">FAQ</h2>
    <h3 style="margin:12px 0 0">Do topic pages replace the calculators?</h3>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:8px 0 0">
      No. They organize the calculators and explain how to interpret results. The calculators are where you run numbers.
    </p>
    <h3 style="margin:12px 0 0">Why are there multiple guides for one topic?</h3>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:8px 0 0">
      Each guide answers a specific question or decision (fees, payoff speed, recast vs extra), so you can focus on one issue at a time.
    </p>
  </section>
  <section class="grid" style="margin-top:18px">
    <div class="card section prose col-6 topic-card">
      <h2 style="margin-top:0">APR & borrowing costs</h2>
      <p class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0">
        Compare offers with fees and understand when APR can mislead.
      </p>
      <div class="btn-row" style="margin-top:12px">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/topics/apr">APR topic</a>
        <a class="btn" href="/calculators/apr-calculator">APR calculator</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card section prose col-6 topic-card">
      <h2 style="margin-top:0">Credit cards & payoff</h2>
      <p class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0">
        Model payoff timelines and interest costs with fixed payments.
      </p>
      <div class="btn-row" style="margin-top:12px">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/topics/credit-cards">Credit cards topic</a>
        <a class="btn" href="/calculators/credit-card-payoff-calculator">Payoff calculator</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card section prose col-6 topic-card">
      <h2 style="margin-top:0">Mortgage payment & payoff planning</h2>
      <p class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0">
        Compare extra principal, lump sums, and payoff timelines.
      </p>
      <div class="btn-row" style="margin-top:12px">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/topics/mortgage-payoff">Mortgage payoff topic</a>
        <a class="btn" href="/calculators/extra-payment-calculator">Mortgage payoff calculator</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card section prose col-6 topic-card">
      <h2 style="margin-top:0">Refinance decisions</h2>
      <p class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0">
        Compare closing costs, rates, and break-even timing.
      </p>
      <div class="btn-row" style="margin-top:12px">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/topics/refinance">Refinance topic</a>
        <a class="btn" href="/guides/refinance-break-even">Break-even guide</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card section prose col-6 topic-card">
      <h2 style="margin-top:0">Debt-to-income & affordability</h2>
      <p class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0">
        Calculate DTI and see how to improve your ratio.
      </p>
      <div class="btn-row" style="margin-top:12px">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/topics/debt-to-income">DTI topic</a>
        <a class="btn" href="/calculators/debt-to-income-calculator">DTI calculator</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card section prose col-6 topic-card">
      <h2 style="margin-top:0">Request a topic</h2>
      <p class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0">
        Want a workflow page for a specific question? Email <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="card section prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">What each topic includes</h2>
    <ul class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; padding-left:18px">
      <li>A primary calculator to model the baseline.</li>
      <li>Focused guides that explain assumptions and edge cases.</li>
      <li>Related tools for comparisons and second opinions.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  <section class="card section prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">Before you start</h2>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0">
      Gather your latest statement or loan estimate so you can enter the real balance, rate, and fees. This helps you compare scenarios
      on the same footing and avoid misleading differences caused by stale numbers.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card section prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">Updates</h2>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0">Topics are updated as calculators and guides change. If you want a new workflow, contact us.</p>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:12px 0 0; font-size:13px">Last updated: 2026-01-28</p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
